data.title: Star Wars: The Empire Strikes Back in Concert
data.meta_description: Enter the Star Wars universe, with the NY Phil performing John Williams’s score live to the film. Official Box Office. June 11–14, 2025.
data.text:
There is a limit of 6 tickets per household for these concerts. For groups of 15+ please contact Group Sales at groupsales@nyphil.org or 212.875.5672.

Sarah Hicks’s versatile and vibrant musicianship has secured her place as an in-demand conductor across an array of genres. Her career has seen collaborations with diverse artists, ranging from violinist Hilary Hahn and baritone Dmitiri Hvorostovsky to popular artists cuch as Rufus Wainwright, Jennifer Hudson, and Smokey Robinson. Hicks’s passion for cross-genre partnerships led to her 2019 album with rap artist Dessa and the Minnesota Orchestra, which she serves as principal conductor of its Live at Orchestra Hall series. She has been nominated for two Upper Midwest Emmys as both conductor and host for This Is Minnesota Orchestra.

Learn more about Sarah Hicks
